01:33:06.347 --> 01:33:08.983 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
At the core of that
resolution is an agreement

01:33:09.083 --> 01:33:12.821 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I negotiated in June of
2012 in Geneva, which set

01:33:12.921 --> 01:33:18.259 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
forth a cease-fire and
moving toward a political

01:33:18.359 --> 01:33:22.230 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
resolution, trying to
bring the parties at stake

01:33:22.330 --> 01:33:23.331 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in Syria together.

01:33:23.431 --> 01:33:26.835 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This is incredibly
complicated, because we've

01:33:26.935 --> 01:33:29.871 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
got Iran as a big player,
in addition to Russia.

01:33:29.971 --> 01:33:32.173 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We have Saudi Arabia,
Turkey, and others who

01:33:32.273 --> 01:33:35.343 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
