influence your foreign

01:42:11.125 --> 01:42:12.326 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
policy decisions?

01:42:12.426 --> 01:42:14.462 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And why do you see
them as -- why are they

01:42:14.562 --> 01:42:16.263 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
influential?"

01:42:16.364 --> 01:42:20.234 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SANDERS: You know,
Franklin Delano Roosevelt

01:42:22.436 --> 01:42:28.509 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
took the oath of office
in 1933 at a time when 25

01:42:28.609 --> 01:42:32.246 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
percent of the American
people were unemployed,

01:42:32.346 --> 01:42:34.148 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
country was in
incredible despair.

01:42:34.248 --> 01:42:36.751 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And he stood before the
American people and he

01:42:36.851 --> 01:42:41.389 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
said, "The only thing
we have to fear is fear

01:42:41.489 --> 01:42:46.660 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
itself," a profound
statement that gave the

01:42:46.761 --> 01:42:49.930 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
American people the
courage to believe that,

01:42:50.031 --> 01:42:54.101 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
yes, we could get out of
that terrible depression.

01:42:55.102 --> 01:42:58.939 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And then what he did
is redefine the role of

01:42:59.040 --> 01:43:00.107 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
government.

01:43:00.207 --> 01:43:01.842 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You know, you had Herbert
Hoover before that saying,

01:43:01.942 --> 01:43:03.844 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
no, we got to only
worry about the deficit.

01:43:03.944 --> 01:43:05.913 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
So what if mass
unemployment exists?

01:43:06.013 --> 01:43:07.748 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So what if children
are going hungry?

01:43:07.848 --> 01:43:09.350 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's not the role
of the government.

01:43:10.217 --> 01:43:13.487 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
